### Artifacts naming

Any output produced by a skill or session ‚Äî feedback files, generated documents, collected data, derived artefacts ‚Äî lands under an `artifacts/` directory, never co-located with `workstreams/` or `sessions/`. Artefacts mirror their scope, exactly like workstreams, sessions, and memory: workspace-scoped artefacts at the workspace root, project-scoped artefacts under the project.

| Output type | Path pattern |
|-------------|--------------|
| Skill output, workspace scope | `artifacts/<skill-slug>/<filename>` (e.g., `artifacts/one-on-one-prep/2026-05-11-jane.md`) |
| Skill output, project scope | `projects/<project-slug>/artifacts/<skill-slug>/<filename>` |
| Workstream artefact, workspace scope | `artifacts/<workstream-slug>/<filename>` |
| Workstream artefact, project scope | `projects/<project-slug>/artifacts/<workstream-slug>/<filename>` |

Separation of concerns: `workstreams/` files are open-item ledgers that `/bye` writes into; mixing observational output pollutes that lifecycle. Resolve scope from the session marker, never from cwd.

